entry.def: Traffic refers to all the vehicles that are moving along the roads in a particular area.

example.ex: There was heavy traffic on the roads...
Traffic was unusually light for that time of day.
example.tran: 对于一天中的那个时间段而言，来往车辆少得有些不寻常。

entry.def: Traffic refers to the movement of ships, trains, or aircraft between one place and another. Traffic also refers to the people and goods that are being transported.

example.ex: Air traffic had returned to normal...
The railways will carry a far higher proportion of freight traffic...
example.tran: 铁路将承担比例高得多的货运量。

entry.tran: (毒品、赃物等的)非法买卖，非法交易
entry.def: Traffic in something such as drugs or stolen goods is an illegal trade in them.

example.ex: Traffic in illicit drugs was now worth some 500 thousand million dollars a year.
example.tran: 如今每年非法毒品的交易值约在 5,000 亿美元。

entry.def: Someone who traffics in something such as drugs or stolen goods buys and sells them even though it is illegal to do so.

example.ex: The president said illegal drugs are hurting the entire world and anyone who traffics in them should be brought to justice.
example.tran: 总统称毒品正在危害整个世界，任何非法贩卖毒品的人都应依法受到惩处。
